Description: Double-barrel handle of Koan pottery transport amphora. Rectangular stamp; club symbol.
Curator's comments: Only known from Petrie's drawing in his Journal, 1884-5, p.200, 66. Name, Antinoos? The closest parallel, Alexandria Museum ABC1186, has only Antin.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0098)
